# Platform console layout (desktop)

The platform admin UI lives under `src/app/(platform)/` with a fixed 220px sidebar. **On desktop (`md+`), page content must use the full remaining viewport width** — do not center content in a narrow column.

## Layout shell

- `(platform)/layout.tsx` wraps children in `w-full px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8` — **no `max-w-*` or `mx-auto`** on the shell.
- Sidebar offset is handled by `md:ml-[220px]` on `<main>`.

## Page patterns

```tsx
// ✅ List / table pages — stretch edge to edge inside main padding
<div className="w-full space-y-6">
  <header>...</header>
  <div className="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-[#1e2023]">
    <table className="w-full text-sm">...</table>
  </div>
</div>

// ✅ Dashboard — cards and panels span full width
<div className="w-full space-y-8">
  <div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">...</div>
</div>

// ❌ Avoid on platform pages
<div className="mx-auto max-w-6xl">...</div>
<div className="mx-auto max-w-2xl">...</div>
```

## Forms

- Prefer full-width form cards with responsive grids (`sm:grid-cols-2`, `lg:grid-cols-3`) instead of capping the whole page with `max-w-2xl`.
- Only use a local `max-w-*` on a specific inner widget (e.g. a modal) when narrow width is required for UX — never on the page root.

## Visual tokens

- Background: `#111316` (page), `#1e2023` (cards/panels)
- Borders: `border-white/10`
- Accent: violet (`text-violet-300`, `bg-violet-600`)
